{"TopicId":146533,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"Devnote Thursday: Tweaking and Turning Gears","CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T18:43:25Z","PageNum":4,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Skalou","CreatedById":133496,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:21:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163338\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138353\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HoloYolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, HoloYolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLife support should stay a mod. This game isn\u0027t meant to be 100% realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat\u0027s what people said for communication relay, aerodynamic(\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E in 0.90), heatshield, fairings, ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027m sure there is a way to do life support fun and affordable even for beginers. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:22:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163338\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138353\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HoloYolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, HoloYolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLife support should stay a mod. This game isn\u0027t meant to be 100% realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow I play the PS4, mods are not expected, unfortunately. But when I played on the PC, TAC LS\u00A0I had in a mandatory set.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:28:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133496\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Skalou\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Skalou said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat\u0027s what people said for communication relay, aerodynamic(\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E in 0.90), heatshield, fairings, ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027m sure there is a way to do life support fun and affordable even for beginers. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\naffordability is not the issue.\u00A0 Fun is very much the issue, and life support is not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redneck","CreatedById":2030,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:31:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729578\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472151159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jarin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Jarin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny word on PorkJet\u0027s work with the rocket-part models?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I would like to know also. Ive asked this question in 4 different devnotes this being the 5th. Squad will not answer this question. Why?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729877\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163620\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey aren\u0027t answering the question because it\u0027s not coming in the next version.\u00A0 If it were, we would have heard before QA started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat difference does it make what version it comes out in? I am asking about any progress that has been made regardless of version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:34:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729898\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222030\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Redneck\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Redneck said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat difference does it make what version it comes out in? I am asking about any progress that has been made regardless of version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the DevNotes are mostly concerned with the upcoming version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redneck","CreatedById":2030,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:37:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164474\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the DevNotes are mostly concerned with the upcoming version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I should make a seperate thread then? If they wont answer it here.....whats the point?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729906\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222030\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Redneck\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Redneck said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I should make a seperate thread then? If they wont answer it here.....whats the point?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey will tell us when they are ready to tell us and not before, that\u0027s the point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Perry Apsis","CreatedById":97519,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:41:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\naffordability is not the issue.\u00A0 Fun is very much the issue, and life support is not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould we possibly allow for some difference of opinion on this issue? Personally, I would have said the same thing about money. In fact, I did. Now I use settings that make it so money doesn\u0027t affect my gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like playing with life support, and I would enjoy having a stripped down version in stock. I\u0027m sure it would be optional if it were implemented.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:43:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729911\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297519\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Perry Apsis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Perry Apsis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould we possibly allow for some difference of opinion on this issue? Personally, I would have said the same thing about money. In fact, I did. Now I use settings that make it so money doesn\u0027t affect my gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like playing with life support, and I would enjoy having a stripped down version in stock. I\u0027m sure it would be optional if it were implemented.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with \u0022It will be optional\u0022 is that part loading is not optional and life support requires a lot of parts.\u00A0 No feature that requires parts is completely optional.\u00A0 As far as difference of opinions, we have that.\u00A0 My opinion is no life support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T22:44:34Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 10:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:45:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\naffordability is not the issue.\u00A0 Fun is very much the issue, and life support is not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd what a fun in\u00A0flying on the\u00A0tediuous\u00A0curved\u00A0orbits?\u00A0Let\u0027s fly in straight lines, it is easy and fun!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T23:03:27Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 11:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbuvim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729920\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472165141\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbuvim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Kerbuvim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd what a fun is\u00A0flying on the\u00A0tediuous\u00A0curved\u00A0orbits?\u00A0Let\u0027s fly in straight lines, it is easy and fun!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will find I don\u0027t make points against strawmen.\u00A0 Might as well not place them, I just step around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T22:47:02Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 10:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:50:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729802\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472160349\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jarin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jarin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTop tier cores have \u0022target\u0022 and \u0022maneuver\u0022 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E options, in addition to all the others, which makes them very easy to pilot with only local\u00A0control. If you need less thrust, you can modify the engine\u0027s max thrust directly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but... I don\u0027t fancy landing on a vacuum body above 0.5g with only a binary choice of 0 or 2 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E. (Plenty of these available via Kopernicus!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FullMetalMachinist","CreatedById":156531,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:04:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472165440\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but... I don\u0027t fancy landing on a vacuum body above 0.5g with only a binary choice of 0 or 2 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E. (Plenty of these available via Kopernicus!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have lots of options.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) Land your probe such that it has line of sight with Kerbin\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) Use a satellite in orbit to relay the signal from the probe to Kerbin if you can\u0027t get line of sight directly.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Have a mothership in order that has a pilot Kerbal aboard to control the probe.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4) Turn off the telemetry system altogether.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure that there are more possibilities, but that\u0027s the point, isn\u0027t it? To add more gameplay mechanics which make the game more fun? And if you don\u0027t like it, or don\u0027t like exactly how it is implemented, then turn it off or mod it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Skalou","CreatedById":133496,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:06:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\naffordability is not the issue.\u00A0 Fun is very much the issue, and life support is not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor me it is \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit forces me to find a nice balance between pure efficiency trajectories and time, bi-elliptic transfert or ejection burn cut in dozen pieces for manned? no more...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoverDude","CreatedById":105198,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:07:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472165440\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but... I don\u0027t fancy landing on a vacuum body above 0.5g with only a binary choice of 0 or 2 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E. (Plenty of these available via Kopernicus!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen set up a relay in advance if you are concerned you will be occluded on your descent. \u00A0Or get creative with your engine tweakables \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rub with a probe core that bypasses all restrictions is that in sandbox, it becomes the only probe core you actually use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:12:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472166422\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoverDude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, RoverDude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen set up a relay in advance if you are concerned you will be occluded on your descent. \u00A0Or get creative with your engine tweakables \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rub with a probe core that bypasses all restrictions is that in sandbox, it becomes the only probe core you actually use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remember relays from 0.90 with remote tech... the satellite always left LoS before I landed \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s ok, if I don\u0027t get on with it, I will just turn that feature off and go on with my life \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Errol","CreatedById":118622,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:13:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472152329\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoverDude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, RoverDude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your probe has control, you\u0027re fine. \u00A0The control locks only kick into play when you lose your connection (via occlusion or lack of signal strength). \u00A0By the way, I was able with the auto pilot to very creatively align to a node, even when occluded - was just a bit tricky \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 of course your best bet is to make sure you have signal and pre-align.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we get more information on how signal strength will affect gameplay or other things in game?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\naffordability is not the issue.\u00A0 Fun is very much the issue, and life support is not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah no. Life support for you isn\u0027t fun, sure, fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are a lot of us, mainly everyone that uses an LS mod, that think life support is fun.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T23:37:42Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 11:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Errol\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:24:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472166811\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Errol\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Errol said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we get more information on how signal strength will affect gameplay or other things in game?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, for example - increase in electricity consumption in the weak-signal gain with increasing distance from the signal source ... With many years of flying on batteries or small solar panels, small probe can suddenly turn out to be completely de-energized.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T23:29:19Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 11:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbuvim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fobok","CreatedById":73999,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:24:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m really liking the sound of these changes, especially the radio system. Like a low difficulty Remotetech, which is just what I\u0027m looking for. (Up to now I basically take the mod as it is and turn the difficulties down, this time I\u0027m using the SETI rebalance settings.) As long as Mech Jeb still works, and unmanned satellites can work as relays (I only saw manned capsules mentioned earlier), this will fit me just perfectly. :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:31:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472160980\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope not.\u00A0 Life support and KSP do not fit together, it adds tedium and no gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgree to disagree. \u00A0I think anything more on the subject has been said before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163338\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138353\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HoloYolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, HoloYolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLife support should stay a mod. This game isn\u0027t meant to be 100% realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost of the LS mods aren\u0027t 100% realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729877\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163620\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey aren\u0027t answering the question because it\u0027s not coming in the next version.\u00A0 If it were, we would have heard before QA started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep. \u00A0It\u0027s been clear for a while that the parts overhaul isn\u0027t coming this update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"luizopiloto","CreatedById":97503,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:39:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow will wheels and Legs perform in 1.2? any update? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:40:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLanding a probe without signal will be pretty easy; you have engine on and off controls, and can use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E commands like \u0022point retrograde\u0022, if I\u0027m reading this correctly. Sure, you can\u0027t land it exactly where you\u00A0want it, but it\u0027s certainly not a super-difficult task.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, this game could use life support for the extra detail, and fun, it offers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlphaMensae","CreatedById":152463,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:44:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729877\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163620\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey aren\u0027t answering the question because it\u0027s not coming in the next version.\u00A0 If it were, we would have heard before QA started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter today\u0027s Squadcast, I\u0027m more inclined to think\u00A0this is the case. \u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0has been showing\u00A0a proto-version of 1.2, not even a buid, but something that runs inside the Unity editor. \u00A0Someone in chat asked if it was merely 1.1.3 with some 1.2 features hacked in, but NK said nope, it really was 1.2...and there was no sign of any revamped parts, everything was just the same as before . \u00A0Now, it could be that they weren\u0027t loaded in or otherwise not ready yet, but it\u0027s looking more and more likely the new parts will be in 1.3 (if there is one).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"basic.syntax","CreatedById":109920,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:52:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472165038\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729911\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472164882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297519\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Perry Apsis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, Perry Apsis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like playing with life support, and I would enjoy having a stripped down version in stock. I\u0027m sure it would be optional if it were implemented.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with \u0022It will be optional\u0022 is that part loading is not optional and life support requires a lot of parts.\u00A0 No feature that requires parts is completely optional.\u00A0 As far as difference of opinions, we have that.\u00A0 My opinion is no life support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think LS is a \u0022missing\u0022 part of the\u00A0stock KSP experience,\u00A0which has many consumables that can\u00A0run out, and lead to rescue missions.\u00A0 If a future Squad LS were implemented as a mod, then we could choose to install the parts, or not. I think that would be the best way to go. I would further suggest new\u00A0checkbox options in game settings to automatically download / install / enable official mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T23:52:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat notes! I sadly have to gloss over most of the notes as I fly in and out of signal range in Yosemite, but I want to thank Nightingale for adding the custom difficulty settings to the main menu (should be amazing for KCT and the likes), as well as to Claw for fixing black hole ablator! I sadly can\u0027t tag names on mobile so I\u0027ll have to hope you see this. Also another shout out to Porkjet who although isn\u0027t named this week, I\u0027m sure is hard at work with the hinted at part revamps to come. Take care everyone \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}